               <p>WALTER LEA. On the 17th of June, about ten o'clock in the evening, I was walking through a court, leading from <placeName id="t18260622-222-crimeloc1136">Bartholomew-close</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-222-crimeloc1136" type="placeName" value="Bartholomew-close"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-222-crimeloc1136" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-222-off1134 t18260622-222-crimeloc1136"></join> - I felt my handkerchief slipping from me - I turned round and saw the prisoner with a person who handed the handkerchief to him - I accused the prisoner of having it - he ran off - I followed him through Jewin-street into a court which had no thoroughfare, and secured him; I had not lost sight of him, and am certain he is the person who had it - but I have not seen it since.</p>
               <p>
            
